                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d147">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">399.10–<gloss target="#t_UPU1">UPU</gloss>/1–2351:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Egypt</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <gloss target="#t_niact1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">niact</hi>
                        </gloss>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-01-24T15:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 24, 1951—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>707. For Caffery and Redding. <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> has taken fol
                    action re <gloss target="#t_urtel1">urtel</gloss> 766. Mission Rio requested ask
                        <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> instruct its delegate second and
                    speak in favor US motion. Mission Hague asked endeavor obtain Dutch affirmative
                    vote. In view Bern’s tel Jan 23 rptd Cairo <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss>
                    doubts second approach Swiss wld be fruitful. <gloss target="#t_Dept1"
                        >Dept</gloss> also doubts desirability second approach London or approach
                    Belgrade. Suggest Caffery continue endeavor obtain affirmative vote Egypt.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
